node.title: 'Testament to resilience, strength and unity': Yuwaalaraay/Euahlayi win native title
node.description: The Federal Court of Australia has granted the Yuwaalaraay/Euahlayi people native title rights to nearly 13,000 hectares of land in south west Queensland.

node.title: Aussie legend tops 50th Golden Guitar nominations
node.description: Big names like Troy Cassar-Daley, Amy Shark, Keith Urban and the Wolfe Brothers are up for the top gongs, with local legends also set to hit the stage.

node.title: NZ must help Pacific fight vaccine misinformation - researcher
node.description: NZ and other countries must combat rampant vaccine misinformation in the Pacific, which threatens the whole region, a researcher says. Audio

node.title: N.Y.C. Severs Ties With Housing Boss Who Earned $1 Million a Year
node.description: The city will no longer work with CORE Services Group, the nonprofit run by Jack A. Brown to provide housing and services to the homeless.

node.title: Arizona AG Asks Reporter If They Have STD Rather Than Answer If He Has Gotten COVID Vaccine
node.description: "The question should be, once you allow or cede this authority to the federal government, where does it stop?" Mark Brnovich said at a news conference Monday.

node.title: Judge Orders Medicaid Coverage Be Allowed For Certain Sex Reassignment Surgeries
node.description: The ruling is a "historic win" to the ACLU of Iowa, mandating Medicaid cover gender reassignment surgeries prescribed as a treatment for gender dysphoria.

node.title: 'Threatened our democracy': Alex Jones, Roger Stone subpoenaed in January 6 probe
node.description: A committee investigating the January 6 Capitol insurrection in the US issues subpoenas to five more people, including Donald Trump's ally Roger Stone and conspiracy theorist Alex Jones.

node.title: Cricket Australia's treatment of Tim Paine 'appalling', Cricket Tasmania says
node.description: The board of Cricket Tasmania condemns the treatment of former Test captain Tim Paine by Cricket Australia, saying the national body regarded him as "dispensable".

node.title: Pauline Hanson joins the government to block federal ICAC bill
node.description: The federal government narrowly defeats an attempt by the Senate crossbench, Greens and Labor to kickstart a debate on a national integrity commission.

node.title: Jury hears closing arguments in Ahmaud Arbery murder trial
node.description: Prosecutors said the defendants "assumed the worst" about 25-year-old Ahmaud Arbery before pursuing and attacking him.

node.title: Actor Kevin Spacey to pay $31m to studio after abuse claims
node.description: A mediator has ordered Kevin Spacey to pay nearly $US31 million ($44.6m) to the studio that made the hit Netflix show, House of Cards, for breach of contract following sexual harassment allegations…

node.title: Mt Messenger bypass deal 'risks setting precedent' for more native trees to be destroyed
node.description: It's feared a deal to get the Mt Messenger bypass built in North Taranaki could see more native forests bulldozed for new roads.

node.title: Baby dies of Covid-19 in Fiji as govt eases curfew restrictions
node.description: A three-month-old baby has died of Covid-19 in Fiji. The infant's death brings the country's death toll from the virus to 695.

node.title: U.S. Returns Over 900 Confiscated Artifacts to Mali
node.description: A Homeland Security investigation had discovered funerary objects, Neolithic relics and more in a shipping container in 2009.

node.title: Victims at Christmas Parade Were Young Musicians and Dancing Grannies
node.description: Five adults died in Waukesha, Wis., and at least 10 children were in intensive care. Three were members of a Milwaukee dance troupe, which celebrated grandmothers.

node.title: Chun Doo-hwan, Ex-Military Dictator of South Korea, Dies at 90
node.description: The country’s most vilified former military dictator, he seized power in a coup and ruled his country with an iron fist for most of the 1980s.

node.title: Kevin Spacey ordered to pay $US30 million for House of Cards losses
node.description: The studio behind House of Cards had to fire Spacey for sexual misconduct, halting the production of the show's sixth season and forcing a rewrite to remove his central character.

node.title: Speaker regarded as country's 'finest' steps down, as a little-known backbencher takes his place
node.description: A relatively unknown Queensland LNP member takes the mantle of speaker, after the MP regarded across the political aisle as one of the finest speakers since federation quits the position.

node.title: Northern Territory records 3 new COVID cases, infant taken to Royal Darwin Hospital
node.description: The three new infections are all connected to known cases from Katherine and Robinson River, while authorities say a man who tested positive yesterday contracted the virus from a fish and chip shop exposure site.

node.title: BOM declares La Niña as the east prepares for another sodden end to the week
node.description: We've finally reached La Niña threshold, indicating conditions are primed for rain. On cue, the east is expecting heavy rainfall over the coming days with more flooding on the cards.

node.title: PM confident DHBs can cope with Covid-19 during summer break
node.description: Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern says she is confident that district health boards will be able to cope with Covid-19 pressures over the summer. Audio

node.title: NZ, Aus must help Pacific fight vaccine misinformation - researcher
node.description: New Zealand, Australia and others in the region need to do more to combat rampant vaccine misinformation in Pacific Island countries, a researcher says. Audio

node.title: Auckland wraps its head around reopening
node.description: Auckland is preparing to open for business and tourism hotspots are looking forward to travellers from the region. Meanwhile, providers in South Auckland are still working to boost the vaccination… Audio

node.title: The Problem of Political Despair
node.description: Hopelessness about our democracy could accelerate its decay.

node.title: Lawyers Clash Over Whether Pursuit of Arbery Was Justified
node.description: In closing arguments on Monday, prosecutors also raised a racial motive for why the three white men accused of murdering Ahmaud Arbery began chasing him.

node.title: New Mexico Schools Varying Thresholds When Deciding to Go Remote After COVID Breakouts
node.description: As COVID cases are on the rise in some areas across the country, two New Mexico school districts are shifting to virtual learning before Thanksgiving.

node.title: Neglect Charges Dismissed Against Leaders of Veterans Home in COVID Deaths of 76
node.description: Judge Edward McDonough Jr. said elder abuse laws cannot be applied to administrators, that they are only meant for those giving direct care to the elderly.

node.title: Louisiana Still Waiting For $595M in Federal Hurricane Relief Money More Than a Year Later
node.description: While waiting for aid, plans have been announced to use $11.3 million for housing repair and rebuilding programs for the city of Lake Charles.

node.title: Families of Parkland School Massacre Victims Settle With FBI Over Its Failure to Stop Gunman
node.description: A month after Nikolas Cruz pleaded guilty to 17 counts of murder, attorneys for the families of those killed announced a settlement has been reached.

node.title: Anaesthetics team missed 'constellation of signs' leading to death of 19-mth-old girl
node.description: A coronial inquest has found the death of a 19-month-old girl at Port Macquarie Base hospital two years ago could have been prevented.
